properties.name: sExportName
desc: The export name of the symbol.

properties.name: sSymbolSet
desc: Specifies the name of the symbol set to which this symbol belongs.

properties.name: nCharacter
desc: Specifies the Unicode character of the symbol.

properties.name: sFontName
desc: Specifies the exact name of the font (\"Arial\", \"Courier\", etc.).

properties.name: nCharSet
desc: Specifies the character set which is supported by the font.

properties.name: nFamily
desc: Specifies the general style of the font.

properties.name: nPitch
desc: Specifies the pitch of the font.

properties.name: nWeight
desc: Specifies the thickness of the line.

The allowed integer values correspond as follows: 0 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.DONTKNOW 1 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.THIN 2 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.ULTRALIGHT 3 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.LIGHT 4 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.SEMILIGHT 5 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.NORMAL 7 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.SEMIBOLD 8 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.BOLD 9 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.ULTRABOLD 10 : com.sun.star.awt.FontWeight.BLACK

properties.name: nItalic
desc: Specifies if the font is italic.
The values com.sun.star.awt.FontSlant.REVERSE_OBLIQUE and com.sun.star.awt.FontSlant.REVERSE_ITALIC may not be used.
